01:53.614 --> 01:56.784
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:56.850 --> 01:58.386
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

01:58.452 --> 01:59.887
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

01:59.953 --> 02:02.190
* NA-NA NA NA NA-NA NA *

02:02.256 --> 02:06.126
* NA-NA NA-NA NA
NA-NA NA-NA NA *

02:10.764 --> 02:14.268
WOW! THE BOSEPHEUS
JUMBO WRESTLING BOWL.

02:14.335 --> 02:15.636
IT'S EVERY WRESTLING
FAN'S DREAM,

02:15.703 --> 02:19.173
AND IT--IT'S JUST
SO BEAUTIFUL.

02:19.240 --> 02:20.641
HEY, SCOOB,

02:20.708 --> 02:22.943
LIKE, I SURE WISH WE COULD
FILL THAT JUMBO BOWL

02:23.010 --> 02:24.545
WITH SOME JUMBO CEREAL.

02:24.612 --> 02:26.280
REAH, CEREAL.

02:30.218 --> 02:33.120
THEY'RE DREAMING ABOUT
GIANT CEREAL AGAIN,
AREN'T THEY?

02:33.187 --> 02:34.688
DO THEY EVER STOP?

02:34.755 --> 02:35.989
COME ON, YOU GUYS.

02:36.056 --> 02:38.025
WRESTLING IS A VERY
SERIOUS BUSINESS,

02:38.091 --> 02:39.827
AND--HEY,

02:39.893 --> 02:42.363
IT'S SPARROW MAN!

02:42.430 --> 02:44.498
NOW LISTEN HERE,
MY FINE-FEATHERED FRIEND,

02:44.565 --> 02:47.134
YOU AND YOUR TIGHTS
WORKS FOR ME,

02:47.201 --> 02:49.970
SO I EXPECT YOU
TO WRESTLE TONIGHT!

02:50.037 --> 02:51.372
NO WAY.

02:51.439 --> 02:53.106
WE'RE NOT WRESTLING WITH
THAT MONSTER RUNNING AROUND.

02:53.173 --> 02:54.808
YOU HAVE TO CANCEL
TONIGHT'S MATCH.

02:54.875 --> 02:57.378
Scooby & Shaggy:
MONSTER?
Fred: CANCEL?

02:57.445 --> 02:59.813
YOU MIGHT NOT HAVE HAD
THIS PROBLEM, SWEETIE...

02:59.880 --> 03:02.149
IF YOU WOULD'VE MADE US
THE STAR ATTRACTION.

03:02.216 --> 03:03.884
WHAT KIND OF MONSTER
IS IT?

03:03.951 --> 03:05.319
OH, HEH HEH HEH.

03:05.386 --> 03:08.088
WELL, IT'S NOT A MONSTER,
PER SE, DARLING.

03:08.155 --> 03:09.156
IT'S JUST A--

03:09.223 --> 03:11.124
THE TITANIC TWIST.

03:11.191 --> 03:12.993
SOMEONE TELL ME THAT
THAT'S JUST THE NAME

03:13.060 --> 03:14.662
OF A TOTALLY
AWESOME SLURPEE.

03:14.728 --> 03:15.929
HARDLY.

03:15.996 --> 03:18.232
THE TITANIC TWIST
WAS A WRESTLING MOVE
SO DANGEROUS,

03:18.299 --> 03:19.500
SO BONE-CRUSHING,

03:19.567 --> 03:21.235
THAT IT WAS OUTLAWED
YEARS AGO

03:21.302 --> 03:23.471
AFTER THE ONLY TIME
IT WAS EVER USED.

03:23.537 --> 03:25.406
THE POOR WRESTLER
WHO FELL VICTIM TO IT

03:25.473 --> 03:26.907
NEVER KNEW WHAT HIT HIM.

03:26.974 --> 03:29.142
AND NOW,
AFTER ALL THESE YEARS,

03:29.209 --> 03:30.878
HIS GHOST HAS COME BACK.

03:30.944 --> 03:33.046
AN EVIL CONTORTED BEAST,

03:33.113 --> 03:35.416
SEEKING REVENGE
ON THE WRESTLING WORLD

03:35.483 --> 03:37.618
FOR TURNING
THEIR BACKS ON HIM.

03:37.685 --> 03:40.588
CAN'T YOU JUST POSTPONE
THE MATCH UNTIL YOU
CAPTURE THE MONSTER?

03:40.654 --> 03:41.989
NO!
NO!

03:42.055 --> 03:45.859
LITTLE LADY,
I GOT TOO MUCH RIDING
ON THIS NIGHT TO CANCEL.

03:45.926 --> 03:48.996
BESIDES, I'M BETTING
THIS LITTLE TWISTY FELLA

03:49.062 --> 03:50.431
IS GOOD FOR PUBLICITY.

03:50.498 --> 03:52.866
WELL, COUNT ME OUT,
BOSEPHEUS.

03:52.933 --> 03:54.335
I'M NOT GONNA WRESTLE.

03:54.402 --> 03:56.737
OH, WH-WHERE I'M GONNA
FIND SOMEONE ELSE

03:56.804 --> 03:58.038
ON SUCH SHORT NOTICE?

03:58.105 --> 03:59.340
AHEM!

04:00.708 --> 04:02.142
UM, FRED?

04:02.209 --> 04:03.243
WHERE DID YOU
GET THAT?

04:03.311 --> 04:04.712
OH, THIS?
HEH HEH.

04:04.778 --> 04:08.148
IT'S MY "IN CASE
OF AN EMERGENCY"
WRESTLING COSTUME.

04:08.215 --> 04:09.182
NEAT, HUH?

04:09.249 --> 04:10.451
UM...
INTERESTING.

04:10.518 --> 04:12.185
SHINY.
REAH.

04:12.252 --> 04:13.754
OK, SCIENTIST,

04:13.821 --> 04:15.956
WHAT DO YOU CALL
THIS WRESTLING MOVE?

04:16.023 --> 04:17.291
THE ATOMIC DROP.

04:17.358 --> 04:18.426
OHH!
[CRASH]

04:18.492 --> 04:20.761
THAT'S A GOOD NAME FOR IT.

04:20.828 --> 04:22.596
IT SAYS HERE
THAT ABNER DOUBLEDAY

04:22.663 --> 04:25.198
INVENTED MODERN
WRESTLING IN 1839

04:25.265 --> 04:27.134
WHILE A CADET
AT WEST POINT.

04:27.200 --> 04:28.336
BUT I FIND IT
HARD TO BELIEVE

04:28.402 --> 04:30.003
OUR FUTURE LEADERS
NEEDED TO LEARN

04:30.070 --> 04:32.239
THE FRONT-FACE
BLIZZARD SUFLEX.

04:32.306 --> 04:35.208
UNH! OOH!
OHH. OW.

04:35.275 --> 04:38.245
ACTUALLY, THE FRONT-FACE
BLIZZARD SUFLEX

04:38.312 --> 04:40.948
WAS A FAVORITE MOVE
OF PRESIDENT FORD.

04:41.014 --> 04:42.783
HEY, IT'S
MALACHI CRUNCH.

04:42.850 --> 04:45.386
MR. CRUNCH, I AM
YOUR BIGGEST FAN.

04:45.453 --> 04:46.820
HUNH!
UHH!

04:46.887 --> 04:48.121
GLAD TO HEAR IT, SON.

04:48.188 --> 04:49.623
DAD, I THOUGHT
YOU PROMISED

04:49.690 --> 04:51.291
YOU WEREN'T GOING
NEAR THE RING.

04:51.359 --> 04:53.361
YOU'VE ALREADY WON
THE CHAMPIONSHIP BELT.

04:53.427 --> 04:55.596
YOU DON'T HAVE TO RISK
GETTING INJURED EVER AGAIN.

04:55.663 --> 04:58.332
HEH! YOU'LL HAVE
TO EXCUSE MY KIDS.

04:58.399 --> 05:01.301
SOMETIMES THEY GET
A LITTLE OVERPROTECTIVE.

05:01.369 --> 05:02.603
ARE YOU KIDDING?

05:02.670 --> 05:04.137
WHAT COULD HAPPEN
TO YOU AROUND HERE?

05:04.204 --> 05:05.506
OHH! OHH! OHH!
OHH! OHH! OHH!

05:05.573 --> 05:07.307
COME ON, DAD,
WE'RE LEAVING.

05:07.375 --> 05:08.776
UNH! OOF!

05:08.842 --> 05:11.111
IT SEEMS LIKE IF
ANYONE COULD TAKE
CARE OF HIMSELF,

05:11.178 --> 05:12.312
IT WOULD BE MALACHI.

05:12.380 --> 05:14.147
HE'S THE WORLD
WRESTLING CHAMP.

05:14.214 --> 05:15.349
EVEN I KNOW THAT.

05:15.416 --> 05:17.418
HEY, AND I KNOW
SOMETHING, TOO.

05:17.485 --> 05:19.353
THAT GUY IS SCARY!

05:19.420 --> 05:23.023
ARRR! ARR!

05:23.090 --> 05:25.959
ARRR!

05:26.026 --> 05:26.894
NO!

05:26.960 --> 05:28.028
ARR!

05:28.095 --> 05:31.499
I KNOW ONE WAY
TO STOP A FIGHT.
THE BELL!

05:32.433 --> 05:33.967
[DING DING]

05:38.372 --> 05:40.007
DID YOU SEE
THAT THING?

05:40.073 --> 05:42.676
LIKE, IT HAD 2 ARMS
ON ONE SIDE OF ITS BODY.

05:42.743 --> 05:44.845
HE COULD NEVER
BUY A SHIRT
OFF THE RACK.

05:44.912 --> 05:47.014
OK, GANG. THERE'S
A MISSING WRESTLER.

05:47.080 --> 05:48.315
WHICH MEANS...

05:48.382 --> 05:50.017
WE'VE GOT A MYSTERY
ON OUR HANDS.

05:50.083 --> 05:52.753
I THINK IT'S TIME
WE SPLIT UP
AND LOOK FOR CLUES.

05:52.820 --> 05:54.988
RIGHT, SO WE CAN
SOLVE THIS MYSTERY.

05:55.055 --> 05:57.525
OH, I--I MEANT
SO YOU GUYS
COULD FIND CLUES

05:57.591 --> 06:00.227
AND I COULD
WRESTLE SOME MORE.

06:00.293 --> 06:01.361
BUT I'LL LOOK, TOO.

06:01.429 --> 06:02.596
I MEAN, THAT'S COOL.

06:04.331 --> 06:06.133
[WOLF HOWLING]

06:06.199 --> 06:09.637
SO, THIS IS WHERE
MR. BOSEPHEUS MAKES
THE WRESTLERS LIVE?

06:09.703 --> 06:13.040
HUH. I'LL BET THEY DON'T
EVEN GET CABLE.

06:22.416 --> 06:24.151
ARRR!

06:24.217 --> 06:25.886
IT'S THE TITANIC TWIST!

06:25.953 --> 06:27.087
LIKE HIDE!

06:27.154 --> 06:29.322
ARR ARR ARR ARR.

06:29.389 --> 06:32.560
LIKE, THERE'S ONLY
ONE SAFE PLACE IN
THIS CREEPY COMMUNE--

06:32.626 --> 06:34.394
WHERE THE MONSTER
JUST LEFT.

06:34.462 --> 06:35.729
COME ON, SCOOB.

06:40.300 --> 06:42.402
CANDY.

06:43.637 --> 06:45.973
UH, SURE.
CAN YOU BREAK A 20?

06:46.039 --> 06:48.341
I THINK HE CAN BREAK
ANYTHING HE WANTS.

06:48.408 --> 06:50.310
HEY, IT'S
HUMONGOUS HAMMER.

06:50.377 --> 06:54.281
HE WAS THE BOSEPHEUS
FEDERATION WRESTLING
CHAMP YEARS AGO.

06:54.347 --> 06:55.516
I'M YOUR BIGGEST FAN!

06:55.583 --> 06:59.086
YEP. THAT'S THE WAY
IT GOES AROUND HERE.

06:59.152 --> 07:00.721
ONE DAY YOU'RE THE CHAMP,

07:00.788 --> 07:04.458
THE NEXT DAY YOU'RE INJURED
AND STUCK SELLING RED TWISTS.

07:04.525 --> 07:05.993
WHAT KIND OF INJURY?

07:06.059 --> 07:08.428
TURNBUCKLE KNEE. SEE?

07:08.496 --> 07:09.830
Daphne: OUCH.

07:09.897 --> 07:12.766
YEP. I PUT ON
A GREAT SHOW EVERY NIGHT.

07:12.833 --> 07:15.202
AND HOW DOES OLD BOSEPHEUS
REWARD ME?

07:15.268 --> 07:17.505
BY MAKING ME SELL CANDY.

07:17.571 --> 07:20.107
AND HE KNOWS
I DON'T EVEN LIKE SWEETS.

07:20.173 --> 07:23.443
IF YOU SEE THAT BOSEPHEUS...

07:24.878 --> 07:28.181
WILL YOU TELL HIM THAT
I'M OUT OF BLACK LICORICE?

07:28.248 --> 07:29.983
HMM.
A BITTER EX-CHAMPION

07:30.050 --> 07:32.786
SURE MIGHT WANT
TO STOP THIS EVENT
FROM TAKING PLACE.

07:32.853 --> 07:34.788
I'D SAY THAT MAKES
HIM A SUSPECT.

07:34.855 --> 07:36.990
WELL, THAT AND THE FACT
THAT HE'S HUGE.

07:42.329 --> 07:43.296
HUNH!

07:43.363 --> 07:45.899
RAGGY, MILK SHAKES.

07:45.966 --> 07:48.001
YOU'RE RIGHT,
THOSE ARE MILK SHAKES.

07:48.068 --> 07:49.837
WAY TO GO, SCOOBY-DOO.

07:49.903 --> 07:51.805
SHAKES, AHOY!

07:54.608 --> 07:56.243
ACH! YUCK!

07:56.309 --> 07:57.611
THESE ARE
PROTEIN SHAKES.

07:57.678 --> 07:59.079
THEY TASTE
LIKE CHALK.

07:59.146 --> 08:03.817
BUT THAT'S NOTHING
A LITTLE WHIPPED CREAM
WON'T FIX.

08:03.884 --> 08:06.153
OHH, BUMMER.
IT'S EMPTY.

08:06.219 --> 08:07.755
[YAWNS]

08:07.821 --> 08:11.158
WELL, MAYBE
WE CAN FIND SOME
CARAMEL SAUCE AROUND.

08:11.224 --> 08:13.160
UHH!

08:13.226 --> 08:15.162
RAGGY? UH-OH!

08:15.228 --> 08:17.297
HA HA HA HA HA HA!

08:17.364 --> 08:19.399
[DIABOLICAL
LAUGHTER]

08:19.466 --> 08:21.234
[WHIMPERING]

08:21.301 --> 08:22.402
AAH!

08:22.469 --> 08:24.638
ARR! HA HA HA HA!

08:30.377 --> 08:32.345
OHH! OHH! AAAAAAH!

08:32.412 --> 08:34.147
OHH!

08:34.214 --> 08:36.216
YIKES! RAGGY!

08:36.283 --> 08:37.417
RAGGY!

08:37.484 --> 08:39.920
NIGHTY-NIGHT, OLD PAL.

08:39.987 --> 08:40.954
ERRR!

08:41.021 --> 08:42.856
[HOWLING]

08:50.530 --> 08:51.999
AROO!

08:52.065 --> 08:53.634
[WHIMPERING]

09:02.209 --> 09:04.044
PHEW!

09:04.111 --> 09:05.078
UH-OH!

09:05.145 --> 09:06.614
AROO! OOF!

09:07.581 --> 09:09.783
OHH! OHH!

09:10.951 --> 09:12.620
WHOA!

09:12.686 --> 09:15.255
WHOO-HOO-HOO-HOO!

09:15.322 --> 09:16.356
Fred:
ARE YOU GUYS OK?

09:16.423 --> 09:18.458
WE HEARD
A BIG CRASH.

09:18.525 --> 09:20.460
HMM? CRASH?
WHAT CRASH?

09:20.527 --> 09:22.495
SCOOBY, CAN YOU TELL US
WHAT HAPPENED?

09:22.562 --> 09:25.799
[GROWLING]

09:25.866 --> 09:29.002
TITANIC TWIST PUSHED
THE MALACHI TRAILER
DOWN THE HILL?

09:29.069 --> 09:29.970
UH-HUH.

09:30.037 --> 09:32.005
HEY, SHAGGY,
WHAT ARE YOU HOLDING?

09:32.072 --> 09:35.943
THIS? UH,
SODIUM TRIPTOHYDRO--

09:36.009 --> 09:38.445
THAT DOESN'T SOUND
LIKE WHIPPED CREAM.

09:38.511 --> 09:39.847
THAT'S SLEEPING MIST.

09:39.913 --> 09:41.949
I WONDER WHY IT WAS IN
THE MALACHI TRAILER.

09:42.015 --> 09:45.719
MAYBE IT'S HARD TO SLEEP
WITH TRAILERS CRASHING
AT ALL HOURS OF THE NIGHT.

09:45.786 --> 09:47.755
I THINK IT'S TIME
WE DO A LITTLE RESEARCH

09:47.821 --> 09:49.489
ON MR. MALACHI CRUNCH.

09:49.556 --> 09:52.459
WELL, IF YOU WANT TO KNOW
ABOUT THE GREATEST WRESTLERS
IN THE WORLD,

09:52.525 --> 09:54.461
THERE'S ONLY ONE PLACE TO GO:

09:54.527 --> 09:56.830
THE WRESTLING HALL OF FAME.

09:56.897 --> 09:59.800
LIKE, I DON'T CARE
IF THEY ARE JUST
MANNEQUINS IN TIGHTS,

09:59.867 --> 10:02.069
THIS PLACE
IS DARN SPOOKY.

10:02.135 --> 10:03.336
"VIRTUAL WRESTLING"?

10:03.403 --> 10:05.873
WHAT AN ENLIGHTENED
METHOD OF EXPERIENCING
THE SPORT

10:05.939 --> 10:07.741
WITHOUT
ACTUALLY GETTING...

10:07.808 --> 10:10.010
WHOA! OHH! OHH!

10:10.077 --> 10:11.078
UHH! HURT.

10:11.144 --> 10:13.246
CHECK IT OUT, SCOOB.
THIS CHART SHOWS US

10:13.313 --> 10:15.415
HOW TO PULL THOSE
CRAZY WRESTLING MOVES.

10:15.482 --> 10:16.549
NOW, LET ME SEE.

10:16.616 --> 10:18.618
PULL YOUR ARM
THROUGH HERE,

10:18.686 --> 10:21.154
AND YOU GRAB
MY LEFT LEG.

10:21.221 --> 10:23.957
HA HA HA HA HA HA!

10:24.024 --> 10:25.058
JEEPERS!

10:25.125 --> 10:27.327
IT'S THAT RESTLESS
WRESTLING REJECT.

10:27.394 --> 10:28.528
BUT THAT'S STRANGE.

10:28.595 --> 10:30.397
LOOKS LIKE HE'S
ONLY DESTROYING

10:30.463 --> 10:32.099
THE MALACHI CRUNCH
EXHIBIT.

10:32.165 --> 10:33.433
ZOINKS! WE'RE STUCK!

10:33.500 --> 10:36.369
HA HA HA!
A LITTLE HELP, ANYONE!

10:36.436 --> 10:37.504
[GASPING]

10:37.570 --> 10:39.506
Daphne: OH, NO,
HE SPOTTED US!

10:39.572 --> 10:41.274
IT'S TIME
FOR OUR FALL-BACK PLAN.

10:41.341 --> 10:42.409
FALL BACK!

10:44.111 --> 10:46.513
* THEY'RE GONNA GET YOU
ANYWAY *

10:46.579 --> 10:48.982
* ANY WAY THEY CAN *

10:49.049 --> 10:51.184
* I TOLD YOU ONCE,
I'LL TELL YOU AGAIN *

10:51.251 --> 10:53.386
* THAT IT'S
ALL THE SAME *

10:55.055 --> 10:57.324
* YOU'RE ALL TWISTED *

10:57.390 --> 11:00.260
* YOU'RE ALL TWISTED *

11:00.327 --> 11:01.962
* YOU'RE ALL TWISTED *

11:02.830 --> 11:04.297
* YOU'RE ALL TWISTED *

11:13.306 --> 11:15.542
* THEY'RE GONNA
GET YOU ANYWAY *

11:15.608 --> 11:17.077
* ANY WAY THEY CAN *

11:17.144 --> 11:20.180
* I TOLD YOU ONCE,
I'LL TELL YOU AGAIN *

11:20.247 --> 11:23.851
* THAT'S IT'S
ALL THE SAME *

11:23.917 --> 11:25.652
* YOU'RE ALL TWISTED *

11:25.719 --> 11:27.454
PHEW! THAT SURE
WAS CLOSE.

11:27.520 --> 11:29.990
I THINK
THE MONSTER'S GONE.

11:30.057 --> 11:31.324
OR NOT!

11:33.660 --> 11:35.528
I HEARD
SOME COMMOTION.

11:35.595 --> 11:36.830
EVERYBODY ALL RIGHT?

11:36.897 --> 11:38.598
DID THE MONSTER
DO THAT?

11:38.665 --> 11:40.768
NOPE. THOSE TWO
DON'T NEED ANY HELP

11:40.834 --> 11:42.135
GETTING INTO TROUBLE.

11:42.202 --> 11:44.537
NOW, LET'S SEE.

11:44.604 --> 11:45.773
OHH!
OHH!

11:45.839 --> 11:47.274
THANKS, BIG GUY.

11:47.340 --> 11:49.442
LIKE, WHO KNEW
I HAD A RESET BUTTON?

11:49.509 --> 11:52.412
SEE, DAD, TITANIC TWIST
DESTROYED YOUR EXHIBIT.

11:52.479 --> 11:54.514
THAT MEANS HE'S PROBABLY
COMING AFTER YOU NEXT.

11:54.581 --> 11:58.919
KIDS, I'M NOT GONNA LET
A LITTLE GIANT MONSTER
SCARE ME OFF.

11:58.986 --> 12:01.521
WE JUST DON'T WANT TO
SEE YOU GET HURT, DAD.

12:01.588 --> 12:04.324
I CAN TAKE CARE
OF MYSELF.

12:04.391 --> 12:07.394
OK, GANG,
IT'S TIME TO SPLIT UP
AND LOOK FOR CLUES...

12:07.460 --> 12:08.661
AGAIN.

12:08.728 --> 12:10.397
ONLY THIS TIME,
WE'RE GOING UNDERCOVER.

12:10.463 --> 12:13.366
DO I EVEN WANT TO KNOW?

12:13.433 --> 12:17.270
OOH, THE FEMALE WRESTLER'S
DRESSING ROOM.

12:17.337 --> 12:18.605
HOW GREAT IS THIS?

12:18.671 --> 12:19.807
I WISH I HAD A CAMERA.

12:19.873 --> 12:21.408
I WISH I HAD A MASK.

12:21.474 --> 12:22.442
HERE YOU GO.

12:22.509 --> 12:23.777
UGH!

12:25.312 --> 12:28.548
WOW! MR. BOSEPHEUS
SURE HAS A BIG OFFICE.

12:28.615 --> 12:31.785
THERE'S BOUND TO BE
SOME CLUES IN HERE
SOMEWHERE.

12:35.022 --> 12:35.789
OHH!

12:35.856 --> 12:37.624
SPEAKING OF
BOUND CLUES!

12:37.690 --> 12:38.892
THE SCIENTIST!

12:38.959 --> 12:41.328
GOOD WORK, GUYS.
LET'S WAKE HIM UP.

12:43.931 --> 12:45.933
NO! NO! NO!

12:45.999 --> 12:47.334
GET ME OUT OF HERE!

12:48.635 --> 12:50.703
GREAT!
NOW WE'RE CLUELESS.

12:50.770 --> 12:52.372
FIND ANYTHING?

12:52.439 --> 12:53.807
NOTHING MY SIZE.

12:53.874 --> 12:55.976
HEY! WHAT ARE YOU TWO
DOING IN HERE?

12:56.043 --> 12:57.811
YOU AREN'T
LADY WRESTLERS.

12:57.878 --> 12:59.312
UH, SURE WE ARE.

12:59.379 --> 13:02.415
I'M, UM, I'M BOOKWORM.

13:02.482 --> 13:03.516
AND THIS IS...

13:03.583 --> 13:05.152
FASHION SENSE.

13:05.218 --> 13:06.954
THE LAST THING WE NEED
IS COMPETITION

13:07.020 --> 13:08.588
FROM 2 GIRLY GIRLS.

13:08.655 --> 13:12.993
BUT THERE'S AN EASY WAY
TO SEE IF YOUR STORY
CHECKS OUT.

13:13.060 --> 13:16.629
UNH! UHH! UM, CAN
WE TRY ANOTHER MOVE,
PLEASE?

13:16.696 --> 13:18.265
YOU'RE STRETCHING
MY OUTFIT.

13:18.331 --> 13:19.199
[GASPS]

13:19.266 --> 13:20.267
UNH!

13:20.333 --> 13:23.270
DAPHNE, THE NEW SPRING
FASHIONS ARE HERE.

13:23.336 --> 13:24.671
WHERE?

13:24.737 --> 13:25.973
UNH!

13:28.909 --> 13:31.344
SO I GRAB
UNDER HERE

13:31.411 --> 13:33.446
AND THROW!

13:33.513 --> 13:34.915
HEY, IT WORKS.

13:34.982 --> 13:36.016
WHAT DO YOU CALL
THAT MOVE?

13:36.083 --> 13:37.450
THE FLYING DINKLY.

13:37.517 --> 13:41.188
OK, GUYS, LOOK AROUND
FOR ANYTHING SUSPICIOUS.

13:41.254 --> 13:43.823
LIKE, I THINK THAT'S
DAPHNE AND VELMA
WRESTLING.

13:43.891 --> 13:46.026
YOU'RE RIGHT!
AND I CAN'T BELIEVE

13:46.093 --> 13:48.962
VELMA KNOWS THE OZARK
MOUNTAIN PILE DRIVER.

13:52.599 --> 13:54.701
HEY, IT'S TITANIC TWIST.

13:54.767 --> 13:57.470
GOOD THING IT'S
JUST ON THE MONITOR,
EH, SCOOB? HA HA HA.

13:57.537 --> 13:59.272
I HAD TO SAY IT.

13:59.339 --> 14:01.508
ARRRR!

14:01.574 --> 14:03.243
THAT WAY, FREDDY!

14:03.310 --> 14:05.445
RARR!
AAH!

14:09.816 --> 14:10.783
ZOINKS!

14:10.850 --> 14:13.486
NO NEED TO PANIC, GUYS.

14:13.553 --> 14:14.554
ARRR!

14:14.621 --> 14:16.656
OK, NOW YOU CAN PANIC.

14:16.723 --> 14:18.558
[TITANIC TWIST GROWLING]

14:18.625 --> 14:21.228
FREDDY,
YOU'RE A WRESTLER.
LIKE, DO SOMETHING.

14:21.294 --> 14:24.464
MY MOVES ONLY WORK
ON OPPONENTS WITH
AN ARM ON EACH SIDE.

14:24.531 --> 14:25.498
NOT AGAINST...

14:25.565 --> 14:27.300
CREEPY CONTORTED
CREATURES?

14:27.367 --> 14:29.336
WELL, IT'S A GOOD THING
WE'RE DRESSED AS JANITORS

14:29.402 --> 14:31.771
BECAUSE THINGS ARE
ABOUT TO GET MESSY.

14:31.838 --> 14:33.240
RARRR!

14:35.408 --> 14:36.509
[SHAGGY WHIMPERING]

14:36.576 --> 14:37.544
ARRRR!

14:37.610 --> 14:38.578
OHH! HOO HOO HOO!

14:38.645 --> 14:40.313
RAGGY, RAGGY.

14:41.514 --> 14:42.649
RARRR!

14:42.715 --> 14:45.318
GOOD GOING, SCOOB.

14:45.385 --> 14:46.586
[MOTOR WHIRRING]

14:46.653 --> 14:48.255
RARRR!

14:48.321 --> 14:49.789
AAH!
AAAH!

14:49.856 --> 14:51.925
UNH! UHH! UNH!

14:53.726 --> 14:55.028
RARRR!

14:55.095 --> 14:58.698
Daphne: OH, NO!
TITANIC TWIST HAS FREDDY!

14:58.765 --> 14:59.933
UNH! UHH!

15:00.000 --> 15:01.868
SHAGGY! SCOOBY!
ARE YOU TWO OK?

15:01.935 --> 15:04.437
LIKE, IF MY FOOT IS
SUPPOSED TO BE IN MY EAR,

15:04.504 --> 15:05.738
THEN YEAH.

15:05.805 --> 15:08.741
NOW, WHAT IN THE TARNATION
IS GOING ON UP IN HERE?

15:08.808 --> 15:10.677
I GOT A SELL-OUT TONIGHT,

15:10.743 --> 15:12.612
THANKS TO THAT
WRESTLE MANIAC,

15:12.679 --> 15:15.548
AND I'M NOT ABOUT TO LET
Y'ALL KIDS MESS THAT UP.

15:15.615 --> 15:16.583
OOOH!
OOOOOH!

15:16.649 --> 15:17.617
UHH!
UNH!

15:17.684 --> 15:19.252
NOW GO ON WITH YOU, GIT!

15:21.989 --> 15:23.790
I'VE GOT
A SNEAKING SUSPICION

15:23.856 --> 15:25.292
ABOUT THAT
MR. BOSEPHEUS.

15:25.358 --> 15:27.594
BUT RIGHT NOW WE'VE
GOT TO FIND FRED.

15:27.660 --> 15:29.262
I GUESS WE SHOULD
SPLIT UP?

15:29.329 --> 15:31.164
OH, MAN,
FRED'S NOT EVEN HERE.

15:31.231 --> 15:33.633
WE DON'T NEED TO...
SPLIT UP.

15:33.700 --> 15:35.468
GUYS?

15:35.535 --> 15:38.938
WELL, IF WE'RE GONNA
SEARCH THE WHOLE
JUMBO BOWL FOR FREDDY,

15:39.006 --> 15:40.240
WHAT BETTER PLACE
TO START

15:40.307 --> 15:42.009
THAN THE SALTED
PRETZEL ROOM?

15:42.075 --> 15:45.078
YEAH, SALTED
PRETZEL ROOM.

15:45.145 --> 15:49.016
NOW, REMEMBER, SCOOB...

15:49.082 --> 15:51.985
WE NEED TO FIND FREDDY,
SO EAT FAST.

15:57.057 --> 15:58.658
FREDDY, IT'S YOU!

15:58.725 --> 15:59.826
WHAT DO YOU KNOW,
SCOOB!

15:59.892 --> 16:01.828
FINALLY, OUR
EAT-FAST PLAN WORKED.

16:01.894 --> 16:03.396
RARRR!

16:03.463 --> 16:04.464
AAAH!
AAAH!

16:04.531 --> 16:05.565
WAKE UP, FRED.

16:05.632 --> 16:07.334
OH, WOW,
HE'S REALLY OUT.

16:07.400 --> 16:10.037
SCOOB, WE NEED TO LEAD
THE TWISTED TITAN
OUT OF HERE

16:10.103 --> 16:11.238
AND AWAY FROM FRED.

16:11.304 --> 16:13.673
HEY, TWIST,
ARE YOU LEFT-HANDED

16:13.740 --> 16:15.475
OR LEFT-HANDED?

16:15.542 --> 16:16.776
RARRR!

16:16.843 --> 16:18.778
HUMONGOUS HAMMER
SURE IS SUSPICIOUS.

16:18.845 --> 16:20.980
I MEAN, WHO ELSE
IS BIG ENOUGH
TO BE THE MONSTER?

16:21.048 --> 16:22.649
AAAH!
AAAAH!

16:22.715 --> 16:23.950
RARRR!

16:24.017 --> 16:25.652
AAH!
AAH!

16:25.718 --> 16:27.354
RARR! RARRR!

16:28.755 --> 16:30.323
HUMONGOUS HAMMER?

16:30.390 --> 16:31.658
THANKS FOR
SAVING US.

16:31.724 --> 16:33.126
YOU'RE WELCOME.

16:33.193 --> 16:36.296
SOMETIMES THESE GIANT HANDS
ARE STILL GOOD FOR SOMETHING

16:36.363 --> 16:38.798
BESIDES CLEANING GIANT EARS.

16:38.865 --> 16:41.000
OK. WAIT A MINUTE.

16:41.068 --> 16:44.471
IF YOU'RE HERE,
THAT MEANS YOU CAN'T BE
THE TITANIC TWIST.

16:44.537 --> 16:48.075
AS MUCH AS I'D LIKE
BOSEPHEUS TO GET
WHAT'S COMING TO HIM,

16:48.141 --> 16:50.543
I'D NEVER BE ABLE
TO GET AROUND LIKE THAT,

16:50.610 --> 16:52.712
WHAT WITH MY TURNBUCKLE
KNEE AND ALL.

16:52.779 --> 16:55.548
BUT THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS
TO OLD WRESTLERS.

16:55.615 --> 16:57.084
HMM, YOU KNOW WHAT?

16:57.150 --> 16:59.619
I THINK I HAVE THIS MYSTERY
JUST ABOUT WRAPPED UP.

16:59.686 --> 17:03.590
GREAT! NOW ALL WE NEED
IS A FRED-LIKE TRAP.

17:03.656 --> 17:06.293
HEY, DON'T LOOK AT ME.
I JUST SOLVE THESE THINGS.

17:06.359 --> 17:08.395
AAAH! AAH!
AAAH!
AAAH!

17:08.461 --> 17:11.030
RARRR!

17:11.098 --> 17:14.934
COME ON, SCOOB,
LET'S HIDE IN HERE.

17:15.001 --> 17:16.736
QUICK,
TURN OFF THE LIGHT.

17:16.803 --> 17:18.138
HERE, SCOOB,
PUT SOMETHING ON

17:18.205 --> 17:20.473
SO THAT WRESTLE MANIAC
WON'T RECOGNIZE US.

17:20.540 --> 17:21.508
Scooby: OK.

17:21.574 --> 17:23.643
HEY, I THINK I FOUND
AN ELEVATOR.

17:23.710 --> 17:25.745
THIS COULD BE
OUR TICKET OUT OF HERE.

17:25.812 --> 17:27.147
[CROWD CHEERING]

17:27.214 --> 17:29.749
Announcer: AND NOW,
WHAT YOU'VE BEEN WAITING FOR...

17:29.816 --> 17:33.620
THE TEXAS CAGE MATCH!

17:33.686 --> 17:34.921
CAGE MATCH?

17:34.987 --> 17:36.389
RAGE RATCH?

17:36.456 --> 17:38.758
OOH!

17:38.825 --> 17:39.792
ARRR!

17:39.859 --> 17:41.928
YIKES!
AAAH!

17:41.994 --> 17:44.431
OHH! OHH! OHH!

17:45.732 --> 17:47.200
WHOA-HO-HO!

17:47.267 --> 17:49.302
I DON'T THINK THIS
COULD GET ANY WORSE.

17:49.369 --> 17:51.304
RARRR!

17:52.772 --> 17:53.873
[SCREAMING]

17:53.940 --> 17:55.608
OK, I WAS WRONG.

17:55.675 --> 17:56.809
THIS IS WORSE.

17:56.876 --> 17:58.911
RARR! RARR!

17:58.978 --> 18:00.780
LOOK AT SHAGGY
AND SCOOBY.

18:00.847 --> 18:02.282
WE HAVE TO DO
SOMETHING.

18:02.349 --> 18:03.716
DO YOU HAVE A PLAN?

18:03.783 --> 18:04.751
NO. YOU?

18:04.817 --> 18:05.785
NOPE.

18:05.852 --> 18:07.120
I MISS FRED.

18:07.187 --> 18:09.088
LOOK, OVER THERE!

18:09.156 --> 18:11.124
THE CONTROLS
FOR THE CAGE.

18:13.059 --> 18:15.128
RARRR!

18:17.664 --> 18:19.098
RARR! ARR!

18:19.166 --> 18:20.300
HANG ON!

18:20.367 --> 18:22.469
LIKE, WHAT DO YOU
THINK WE'RE DOING?

18:23.936 --> 18:26.373
WHOA-OH-OH-OH-OH!

18:29.909 --> 18:31.311
UNH!

18:31.378 --> 18:32.078
UHH!

18:32.145 --> 18:34.147
AAH!

18:46.893 --> 18:48.628
RARR!

18:48.695 --> 18:51.164
[MUFFLED] RARR!

18:58.838 --> 19:00.673
OH, MAN,
I MISSED THE TRAP!

19:00.740 --> 19:02.809
AND IT LOOKS LIKE
IT WAS PRETTY COOL.

19:02.875 --> 19:03.843
All: FREDDY!

19:03.910 --> 19:05.512
[ALL TALKING AT ONCE]

19:05.578 --> 19:06.813
RARR.

19:06.879 --> 19:09.115
NOW, LET'S FIND OUT
WHO THE MONSTER IS

19:09.182 --> 19:10.350
AND, MORE IMPORTANTLY,

19:10.417 --> 19:12.919
WHAT PERSON CAN FILL OUT
ALL THIS FABRIC?

19:12.985 --> 19:15.755
NOT WHAT PERSON,
WHAT PEOPLE?

19:16.923 --> 19:18.991
All: CURT AND CONNIE CRUNCH?

19:19.058 --> 19:21.994
KIDS?

19:22.061 --> 19:25.164
THE CRUNCH KIDS WANTED
TO SCARE THEIR FATHER
OUT OF WRESTLING

19:25.232 --> 19:26.866
SO HE WOULDN'T
END UP INJURED...

19:26.933 --> 19:28.435
LIKE HUMONGOUS HAMMER.

19:28.501 --> 19:30.403
THAT'S WHY THEY ONLY ATTACKED
THE MALACHI EXHIBIT

19:30.470 --> 19:32.205
IN THE WRESTLING MUSEUM--

19:32.272 --> 19:35.542
TO MAKE IT LOOK LIKE
HE WAS THE TITANIC TWIST'S
NEXT TARGET.

19:35.608 --> 19:37.677
SO THAT'S HOW
THE MONSTER COULD HAVE

19:37.744 --> 19:39.412
2 ARMS ON ONE SIDE
OF HIS BODY.

19:39.479 --> 19:42.048
BECAUSE THERE
WERE 2 PEOPLE
INSIDE THE SUIT.

19:42.114 --> 19:45.718
BUT HOW DID 2 KIDS
KNOCK OUT ALL THOSE
HUGE WRESTLERS?

19:45.785 --> 19:48.120
IT'S EASY WHEN YOU USE
THE SLEEPING MIST

19:48.187 --> 19:49.956
WE FOUND IN
MALACHI'S TRAILER.

19:50.022 --> 19:51.391
AND THEY GOT AWAY WITH IT,

19:51.458 --> 19:53.693
EVEN IN SPITE
OF YOU MEDDLING KIDS.

19:53.760 --> 19:54.694
HUH?
HUH?

19:54.761 --> 19:55.862
THEY WERE RIGHT.

19:55.928 --> 19:58.331
IT IS ABOUT TIME
THE OLD MAN RETIRES

19:58.398 --> 19:59.932
BEFORE HE GETS HURT.

19:59.999 --> 20:01.468
CURT, CONNIE,

20:01.534 --> 20:03.236
THANKS FOR
LOOKING OUT FOR ME.

20:03.303 --> 20:05.572
[CROWD CHEERING]

20:08.441 --> 20:11.644
NOW, THIS IS WHAT WRESTLING
IS ALL ABOUT, FOLKS.

20:11.711 --> 20:12.979
FAMILY.

20:13.045 --> 20:16.916
LET'S CELEBRATE LIKE ONE BIG
HAPPY WRESTLING FAMILY!

20:16.983 --> 20:18.685
UNH!
OHH!

20:18.751 --> 20:21.087
IT SURE IS NICE
TO SOLVE A MYSTERY,

20:21.153 --> 20:22.922
AND FOR SUCH
A SWEET FAMILY.

20:22.989 --> 20:24.156
YOU SAID IT.

20:24.223 --> 20:27.193
HEY, WHERE'S SCOOBY?

20:27.260 --> 20:29.962
SCOOBY DOOBY...

20:30.029 --> 20:31.731
DOO!

20:31.798 --> 20:33.566
[ALL LAUGHING]
